This project reads data from a CSV file and displays it as a neatly formatted table in Python.
The program asks the user for a file name, checks that it ends with .csv, and reads its contents
line by line. Each line is split by commas and stored in a table. Column widths are calculated dynamically 
so that all values are centered when printed. The table header and rows are displayed with separators for 
clarity. A sample CSV file (do.csv) is included. The project can also be run in Docker using Python 3.11, 
copying the script and CSV file into the container and executing the script on start.